============================================================ --%>
<.legal_page
  title="Terms of Service"
  updated="June 4, 2026"
  summary="The plain version: use emisar lawfully, you own your data and the actions you authorize, and our liability is limited. The full detail is below."
  toc={[
    {"service", "1. The service"},
    {"acceptable-use", "2. Acceptable use"},
    {"billing", "3. Plans and billing"},
    {"confidentiality", "4. Confidentiality"},
    {"disclaimers", "5. Disclaimers"},
    {"termination", "6. Termination"},
    {"governing-law", "7. Governing law"},
    {"updates", "8. Updates to these terms"},
    {"contact", "9. Contact"}
  ]}
>
  <h2 id="service">1. The service</h2>
  <p>
    emisar is a control plane for safely letting AI agents and humans run a
    finite, versioned catalog of operations against your production infrastructure.
    We provide the catalog runtime, the policy engine, the audit journal, and the
    web/API surface you and your AI agents use to interact with them. emisar is
    operated by Andrii Dryga (<strong>"we"</strong>, <strong>"us"</strong>); these
    terms are the agreement between you and us.
  </p>
  <p>
    emisar is <strong>not</strong>
    a general-purpose remote shell, a backup product, a monitoring product, or a substitute for
    your own change-management process. It is the layer between an AI agent's intent and a host's
    execution.
  </p>
  <p>
    The emisar source code (runner and control plane) is published under a
    <strong>source-available license that is not an OSI-approved open-source license</strong>
    — see the LICENSE file in the repository for the exact grant. These terms govern the
    hosted control plane, which is the supported product today.
  </p>

  <h2 id="acceptable-use">2. Acceptable use</h2>
  <p>By using emisar you agree not to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      Use emisar to <strong>evade an audit obligation</strong>
      you owe to your employer, your customers, or a regulator — every action emisar runs is by
      design recorded and exportable, and we will not help you delete that record.
    </li>
    <li>
      Share, publish, or sublicense your API keys or runner enrollment tokens. Each key identifies
      a principal; treat them like passwords.
    </li>
    <li>
      Target hosts, networks, or services you do not own or do not have explicit authorization to
      operate on.
    </li>
    <li>
      Use emisar to violate any applicable law, infringe any third party's rights, or transmit
      malicious software.
    </li>
    <li>
      Attempt to circumvent access controls or the trust boundary between the LLM, the control
      plane, and the runner.
    </li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    We may suspend an account that violates these rules. We will tell you why, and
    we will let you export your data first if the situation allows.
  </p>

  <h2 id="billing">3. Plans and billing</h2>
  <p>
    <strong>Free</strong>
    is free forever for personal and evaluation use, with the limits listed on the
    pricing page (1 user, 3 runners, 7-day audit retention).
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Team</strong>
    is billed monthly via Paddle. You can cancel at any time from your billing
    settings; cancellation takes effect at the end of the current billing period
    and you retain access until then. We do not pro-rate refunds for partial
    months.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Enterprise</strong>
    is contracted directly (invoice, custom terms, deployment planning, longer retention). Email
    <a href={EmisarWeb.MailTo.sales()}>sales@emisar.dev</a>
    to start a conversation.
  </p>

  <h2 id="confidentiality">4. Confidentiality</h2>
  <p>
    Your audit events, action packs, policies, and the contents of any runs you
    execute through emisar are <strong>your confidential data</strong>. We do not
    disclose them to third parties except (a) to the subprocessors listed in the
    Privacy Policy, strictly as needed to operate the service, or (b) when
    compelled by valid legal process, in which case we will notify you in advance
    unless we are legally prohibited from doing so.
  </p>
  <p>
    Our engineers do not access your data except to investigate a support ticket
    you have opened or a security incident in progress. Such access is restricted
    to the engineers who need it and logged at the infrastructure layer.
  </p>

  <h2 id="disclaimers">5. Disclaimers</h2>
  <p>
    The service is provided <strong>"as is"</strong>
    and <strong>"as available"</strong>. We make no warranties of any kind, express
    or implied, including merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, or
    non-infringement.
  </p>
  <p>
    Our security posture is best-effort and improving. We will be transparent about
    incidents and limitations (see our Security page), but we cannot promise that
    no bug, no outage, and no security issue will ever occur.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>You are responsible for the actions you authorize emisar to perform.</strong>
    If a policy you wrote permits an action, and that action runs, and that action
    causes damage to your systems, the responsibility is yours, not ours. emisar's
    job is to be the auditable gate; your job is to define a sensible catalog and
    a sensible policy.
  </p>
  <p>
    To the maximum extent permitted by law, our aggregate liability arising out of
    or relating to the service is limited to the fees you paid us in the twelve
    months preceding the claim, or US $100, whichever is greater.
  </p>

  <h2 id="termination">6. Termination</h2>
  <p>
    You can leave at any time. Cancel your subscription from the billing settings,
    export your data, and email <a href={EmisarWeb.MailTo.support()}>support@emisar.dev</a>
    to delete your account. We retain only what we are legally required to retain.
  </p>
  <p>
    We may terminate or suspend an account that materially violates these terms
    (notably the acceptable-use rules above). For paid plans we will give you a
    reasonable opportunity to cure where the situation allows.
  </p>

  <h2 id="governing-law">7. Governing law</h2>
  <p>
    These terms are governed by the laws of the State of Delaware, United States,
    without regard to its conflict-of-laws provisions. Any dispute arising out of
    or relating to these terms will be brought in the state or federal courts
    located in Delaware, and both parties consent to that jurisdiction.
  </p>

  <h2 id="updates">8. Updates to these terms</h2>
  <p>
    We may update these terms over time. For paid plans we will email registered
    billing contacts at least 30 days before material changes take effect; if you
    do not agree to the new terms you can cancel before they apply. For free
    accounts, the current version on this page governs.
  </p>

  <h2 id="contact">9. Contact</h2>
  <p>
    Questions or concerns: <a href={EmisarWeb.MailTo.support()}>support@emisar.dev</a>.
    Sales and enterprise contracts: <a href={EmisarWeb.MailTo.sales()}>sales@emisar.dev</a>.
  </p>
</.legal_page>
